cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of counting built-structures in satellite imagery using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new dataset for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The attention-based re-weighting technique used in the proposed framework is a popular technique in deep learning, which could also make it relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
